      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>The term <em>handmade</em> usually refers to objects made by hand or by using simple tools rather than machines. The result may be homely — as in a child's clay ashtray — or exquisite, like a hand-embroidered silk gown.</p>

      <h2>History</h2>
      <p>In the past, web pages were built in plain HTML. This simplicity emphasized content and personality over frameworks and automation.</p>

      <h2>Media Archaeology</h2>
      <p>Looking back at early web practices helps us understand design decisions today. The handmade web is about care, intention, and craft.</p>

